# **TAU EMPIRE SPECIAL RULES**

## **Markerlights**

The Tau Empire employs sophisticated targeting systems known as Markerlights to coordinate their firepower with devastating precision. Pathfinders, Marker Drones, and other specialists paint enemy targets with invisible targeting beams, providing real-time firing solutions to the rest of the Hunter Cadre.

### **Markerlight Weapon Profile**

| Weapon | Range | S | AP | Type |
| ----- | :---: | :---: | :---: | ----- |
| **Markerlight** | 36" | — | — | Heavy 1, Markerlight |

**Markerlight:** This weapon does not inflict wounds. Each successful hit places one **Markerlight Token** on the target unit. Tokens remain on the target unit until the end of the current turn.

### **Spending Markerlight Tokens**

Before a unit with the **Supporting Fire** special rule resolves its shooting attacks against a target with one or more Markerlight Tokens, it may spend any number of tokens from that target to gain the following effects for its attacks against that target:

| Cost | Effect |
| :---: | ----- |
| 1 token | Re-roll failed to-hit rolls of 1 |
| 1 token | Target does not benefit from cover saves |
| 1 token | One Seeker Missile may be fired at the firer's full BS (instead of snap fire) |
| 1 token | Reduce scatter distance by D6" for one blast/barrage weapon fired at this target |
| 2 tokens | \+1 BS (may be purchased multiple times; maximum effective BS is 5\) |

Effects are cumulative. The same effect may be purchased multiple times for the same unit (where applicable). Tokens are spent from a shared pool on the target — once spent, they are no longer available for other units.

## **Supporting Fire**

When an enemy unit declares a charge against a friendly unit with the ***Supporting Fire*** special rule, any other friendly units with the ***Supporting Fire*** special rule within 6" of the charged unit may fire overwatch at the charging unit as if they were also a target of the charge. Supporting Fire is resolved as snap fire (hitting on 6+). Units that fire Supporting Fire may spend Markerlight Tokens on the charging unit, but only effects with a cost of 1 token. A unit that fires Supporting Fire may still fire overwatch normally if it is subsequently charged itself.

***Supporting Fire*** is the defining special rule of the Tau Empire's Fire Caste and its integrated drone network. All Tau Empire Infantry, Battlesuit, and Drone units have this rule unless otherwise noted. Auxiliary units (Kroot, Vespid, Gue'vesa, and similar) do not have this rule.

## **Ta'lissera (Bonding Knife Ritual)**

Any unit with the ***Supporting Fire*** special rule and the Infantry or Battlesuit unit type may purchase the **Ta'lissera** upgrade. A unit with the Ta'lissera special rule may attempt to Regroup even if it is below 25% of its starting strength.

## **Ethereal Rules**

An Ethereal is an optional HQ choice. If an Ethereal is included in the army, it **must** be the army's Warlord.

### **Inspirational Presence**

All friendly units with the ***Supporting Fire*** special rule within 12" of the Ethereal may use the Ethereal's Leadership value in place of their own for all Morale, Pinning, and Leadership tests.

### **Invocation of the Elements**

At the start of the Tau player's turn, the Ethereal may declare one of the following invocations. The effect lasts until the start of the Tau player's next turn and affects all friendly units with the ***Supporting Fire*** special rule within 12" of the Ethereal.

| Invocation | Effect |
| ----- | ----- |
| **Storm of Fire** | Units that remained stationary may fire one additional shot with each Pulse weapon (Pulse Rifle, Pulse Carbine, Pulse Pistol). |
| **Sense of Stone** | Units gain Feel No Pain (6+). |
| **Calm of Tides** | Each affected unit may remove one suppression token. |
| **Zephyr's Grace** | Units add \+1" to their movement and may re-roll failed Dangerous Terrain tests. |

### **Price of Failure**

If the Ethereal is slain, all friendly units with the ***Supporting Fire*** special rule within 12" must immediately take a Morale test.

